<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-85F96655-B6A5-4950-B130-B45DC83BA44F" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-85F96655-B6A5-4950-B130-B45DC83BA44F" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title translate="yes" class="- topic/title ">The job does not appear on the Operator panel and is not printed</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="M140852-B298" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Symptom</title><p class="- topic/p ">A job is submitted with the RIP. The data is transferred correctly, but the job does not appear on the operator panel of the printer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The same occurs if you submit a job with the PrintJobSubmitter tool. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">A reboot does not solve the problem. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-3B8895B9-6BB9-45A4-B224-251952987CAD" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Possible cause</title><p class="- topic/p "> The job submitted to the printer was not within specifications, is corrupt or the "Matte printmodes" license is not available. The job was therefore discarded during processing by the controller software. No document was printed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If such a job is submitted, it might block any next job: if you submit a correct job it also might not appear on the operator panel. The printer will not display any message. Printing is not possible anymore. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Aborting a job in the RIP, also results in an incomplete job in the controller. It is strongly advised to not abort the job in the RIP, but to delete the job on the operator panel of the printer. 
</p><note id="GUID-3580292D-EC5A-4AA9-B262-D7D613741AAF" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The current software releases provide no information to the user when such an error occurs. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The job does not appear on the Operator panel and no information is provided to the user about why the job was rejected. 
</p></note></section><section id="SECTION_BC4C9DB1335C400D8CFB6D62C2406122" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Tests/Checks</title><p class="- topic/p "> When issues such as 'jobs do not appear on the Operator panel' are reported by customers, open the 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Datalog.xml</b> file and search for error code 11956 occurrences. See : 
<xref keyref="GetDatalog" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-070DCC02-4548-4B55-8741-14B970925BC5.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>How to get the datalog file</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ErrorDetails</b> parameter value provides additional information about the error cause. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> For instance: 
</p><fig id="GUID-038257E7-9A4C-443E-82D0-94C48CB46B58" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-50F5ACBE-0141-4E08-9586-3CD58B079977-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-50F5ACBE-0141-4E08-9586-3CD58B079977-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">If such an error is present, then the controller has detected an error in the job which can be corrected with the RIP; see the examples below. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If such an error is not present, execute the following checks: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> submit a correct job (a job you printed before). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> reboot the printer and submit a correct job. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">If in both situations the RIP successfully transfers the data to the printer, but the printer does nothing (no info on the operator panel, no printing), then you need to reinstall the printer software (with keep settings). See : 
<xref keyref="InstNonEmpty" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-A62FC1C7-DB98-4850-B7BE-2357F8EDA956.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>11 How to do a system software installation on a non-empty disk</xref> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-2BB63C78-AC2A-41E6-9B4A-78458E4FD184" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Some example ErrorDetails and their solution</title><p class="- topic/p ">. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-4316C372-BAE7-48E5-9838-EF6E72EDC90E" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ErrorDetails = Incorrect job detected: File is corrupted (received file size: (file size) bytes)</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-402F9DE7-7DC1-46D5-8493-3CA6C6A4606D" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="suspect" cols="6" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="25*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col5" colnum="5" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col6" colnum="6" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Index 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Info 
</p></entry><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Diagram 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The file received by the printer does not have the expected size (indicated in the job footer section of the data). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The job transmission between RIP station and printer was probably interrupted before completion. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check if the job transmission was manually cancelled by operator 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Resubmit the job from RIP. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the issue remains, test the connection with the printer using the DotPrint Job Submitter tool. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-326577AA-A3F2-4A17-8E8D-E4BC4E9315BE" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> ErrorDetails = Incorrect job detected: Preview check failed</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-9F59C975-8415-43E4-8F06-2703B1B52990" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="suspect" cols="6" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="25*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col5" colnum="5" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col6" colnum="6" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Index 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Info 
</p></entry><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Diagram 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The preview thumbnail data embedded in the job are not present or corrupted. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the job transmission was manually cancelled by the operator (see note). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Save the job and check with DotPrint Job Viewer tool if the thumbnail can be previewed. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Resubmit the job from RIP. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the issue remains, test the connection with the printer using the DotPrint Job Submitter tool. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table><note id="GUID-22F969A7-C92A-45C4-ABB5-813B852B1ED0" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">For Onyx jobs, preview thumbnail data are located just after the file header (before the image data). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For Caldera jobs, they are located at the end of the file (after the image data). 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-A796E86B-F3FA-4141-B1E8-8DDE8E453042" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ErrorDetails = Incorrect job detected: The job footer command is not valid</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-4458446A-949F-4ABD-9DD2-A383D1D55456" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="suspect" cols="6" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="25*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col5" colnum="5" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col6" colnum="6" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Index 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Info 
</p></entry><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Diagram 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Jobs created with RIPs drivers include a job footer section which is detected by the printer software to check all job data were received. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the job transmission was manually cancelled by the operator . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Save the job and check with DotPrint Job Viewer tool if the job footer command is present. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Resubmit the job from RIP. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the issue remains, test the connection with the printer using the DotPrint Job Submitter tool. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="SECTION_EBBE3702B1EA41279E3215FF1BD848AD" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> ErrorDetails = Incorrect job detected: Roll width is not within range 279400 &lt;= (Roll width) &lt;= 1625600</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_5973C0C9DE1344D79C6A0FB640CB53B5" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="suspect" cols="6" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="25*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col5" colnum="5" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col6" colnum="6" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Index 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Info 
</p></entry><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Diagram 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The RIP sent a job with an incorrect Roll width value in the header. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the RIP driver version matches with the printers software version. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Upgrade the RIP driver or the printer software so they match. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-256E115F-AD1D-4656-9C1C-65E9F76C1500" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> ErrorDetails = Incorrect job detected: MediaType [(mediatype ID)] is not a valid GUID</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-21C8BBF6-29AA-485F-B3BA-AB98ED265F82" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="suspect" cols="6" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="25*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col5" colnum="5" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col6" colnum="6" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Index 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Info 
</p></entry><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Diagram 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The RIP sent a job with an incorrect Media Type ID in the header. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">For 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Onyx</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Click the new button added in the RIP UI to force media synchronization between the RIP and the printer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Caldera</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Click the button in the RIP UI to force media synchronization between the RIP and the printer. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-C4A24FDB-289E-4412-83F4-B3186DBEAABC" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> ErrorDetails = Incorrect job detected: The leading edge (2000000 micrometers) is bigger than 1 meter</title><p class="- topic/p ">2,000,000 micrometers is 2 meters. 
</p><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-7523EA8E-1865-4004-989B-5C3E572118E7" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="suspect" cols="6" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="25*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col5" colnum="5" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col6" colnum="6" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Index 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Info 
</p></entry><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Diagram 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The RIP sent a job with an out-of-range parameter value in the header. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Edit the submitted job in the RIP and use a correct setting. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Resubmit the modified job. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the issue remains, report it to the RIP provider. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-1C64C375-9CB7-402C-966E-B845DD5755E8" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> FLXfinish<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">+</sup> /Matte prints </title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-B2DBCFBA-FE81-4A89-B036-BCC4CE8AE7C1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="suspect" cols="6" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="25*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col5" colnum="5" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col6" colnum="6" colwidth="15*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Index 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Info 
</p></entry><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Diagram 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The file received by the printer is a matte or FLXfinish<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">+</sup> job while the printer does not support the printing of the matte or FLXfinish<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">+ 
</sup>prints.
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Check the license presence for Matte print mode.
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">
</p><p class="- topic/p "> When matte is required, check if the license was ordered and should be still be valid. In case of a temporary license, acquire and apply a new (temporary) license.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> When the matte license is correctly inactive than update the properties of the printer in the RIP driver to prevent jobs being sent with the Matte/FLXFinish<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">+</sup> properties.
</p></entry><entry colname="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> For FLXfinish<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">+</sup> is besides the license also the coniguration in sds of the additional mirror.
</p></entry><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col5" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-73836C4D-2484-4FD5-97D2-724FE6301C68" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-D1B2AB6F-D28F-44A4-8D97-BDE4CEA9B411-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D1B2AB6F-D28F-44A4-8D97-BDE4CEA9B411-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col6" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-0149BAD2-C9BF-4C02-A646-6F8534640351" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">What the software checks</title><p class="- topic/p ">The software checks if the following job header parameters values are within the allowed range: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Print mode. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Media type. 
